# Exercise Image Display with Carousel Logic

The component displays exercise images with a carousel system for external search results. Here's how it works:

## Image Display Structure

When an exercise has images, the component renders:

```jsx
{exercise.images && exercise.images.length > 0 && (
  <div className="relative w-32 h-32 mt-2">
    <img src={exercise.images[currentImageIndex]} 
         alt={exercise.name} 
         className="w-full h-full object-contain" />
```

The image container is a fixed 32x32 unit box with "object-contain" styling to maintain aspect ratio.

## Carousel Navigation

When multiple images exist, navigation buttons appear:

- **Previous Button**: Uses `ChevronLeft` icon, positioned absolutely on the left side at vertical center
- **Next Button**: Uses `ChevronRight` icon, positioned on the right side

The buttons call `handlePrevImage` and `handleNextImage` functions.

## Index Management

The carousel uses state to track position:

```jsx
const [currentImageIndex, setCurrentImageIndex] = useState(0);

const handleNextImage = () => {
  setCurrentImageIndex((prevIndex) => 
    (prevIndex + 1) % (exercises[0]?.images?.length || 1)
  );
};

const handlePrevImage = () => {
  setCurrentImageIndex((prevIndex) => 
    (prevIndex - 1 + (exercises[0]?.images?.length || 1)) % 
    (exercises[0]?.images?.length || 1)
  );
};
```

This uses modulo arithmetic to create infinite looping—incrementing past the last image wraps to the first, and decrementing before the first wraps to the last.

